.01; 95\% CI, 0.00-0.09), nonfatal MI was not a surrogate for all-cause mortality. Nonfatal MI was not a surrogate for all-cause mortality in randomized clinical trials with 2.0 to 3.9 (R2= 0.004; 95\% CI, 0.00-0.08), 4.0 to 5.9 (R2= 0.06; 95\% CI, 0.001-0.16), or 6.0 or more years of follow-up (R2= 0.30; 95\% CI, 0.01-0.55). Conclusions and Relevance: The findings of this meta-analysis do not appear to establish nonfatal MI as a surrogate for all-cause or CV mortality in randomized clinical trials of interventions to treat or prevent coronary artery disease..},
